Notes 

Class of '55: Memphis Rock 'n' Roll Homecoming brings Johnny Cash, Jerry Lee Lewis, 
Roy Orbison, and Carl Perkins -- all members of the Sun Records stable during its 
heyday -- together for an all-star recording session, which finds the quartet 
tackling a mixture of oldies and new material. Highlights include renditions of 
Perkins' "Birth of Rock and Roll," "Sixteen Candles," Waylon Jennings' "Waymore 
Blues," Cash's "I Will Rock and Roll With You," and John Fogerty's "Big Train 
(From Memphis)."
